case_address_found_1: in a drainage canal close to Newton Street
case_circumstances: This young woman was found in a drainage canal. There was about 3-4 inches of water in the canal and her upper body was above water.  She was fully dressed with no discernable injury to her body.  She had been wrapped in a blanket. It is believed that she was dumped at the spot we found her. She wore some jewelry but had no identification or personal belongings.  Exhaustive investigation  over the years has been unable to establish her identification.
